So I&nbsp;havent really blogged in here because I've been renewed with my obsession to my&nbsp; novel.&nbsp; And have been endlesslesly lost in my pursuit to completion.&nbsp; I will not post any excerpts, because I want to get it published.&nbsp; And I clench on to that novel like its another part of my body part.&nbsp; 

In other news.. my novel's grown bigger than me.&nbsp; It's taken on this direction that never in my wildest dreams I&nbsp;thought it would.&nbsp; Its crazy.&nbsp; Its orwelian.&nbsp; Its sci fi even.&nbsp; That.. was purely accidental.&nbsp; And more importantly, its love and philosophy.&nbsp; Politics.&nbsp; Its everything that I am and hope to be. 

I guess, I've been quite inspired from my environmental bio classes/astronomy.&nbsp; And the dark side of the future, where the world is truly headed.&nbsp; The biggest thing that was missing within my novel was the setting.&nbsp;&nbsp; Well, I found it.&nbsp; I&nbsp;know it now.&nbsp; It is the world that shall be.&nbsp; 

There is a big part of nature within my novel as well, because, as I've learned so much that we are more part of nature than&nbsp;some think we are.&nbsp; In fact, I recently learned from my science class that many components/elements found in rocks are the exact same as us.&nbsp; This is absolutely fascinating to me.&nbsp; But not surprising, since the source we all came from was the universe which consists of all these compounds, chemicals, and energy reactions.&nbsp; 

But what else is amazing, is that the earth is not an island for us, but merely a planet that is a participant in the universe.&nbsp; Thus we are not bigger than it, but much smaller.&nbsp;&nbsp; Dear god, incredibly smaller.&nbsp; &nbsp;And despite the power hungry nature our species possesses, one day we will learn that we are tiny compared to nature, and will not withstand some of the things that will come to be.&nbsp;

So the class that I'm truly getting&nbsp;experience out of this semester is my Modern Middle&nbsp;Eastern class.&nbsp; Not only is it rich and interesting, but it is quite insightful.&nbsp; Because I'm so much more educated about&nbsp;the culture that&nbsp;is so prevalent in the news and yet, not many know of.&nbsp;&nbsp;

And I will say my whole perception on Islam and the Muslim culture changed ever so much.&nbsp; In retrospect, my whole perception of the West towards the Muslim culture changed in certain&nbsp;degrees as well.&nbsp; Islam&nbsp;has a beautiful history which when I'm more awake&nbsp;will blog about.

One&nbsp;thing I will say.&nbsp;&nbsp;Biggest misconception people&nbsp; have about&nbsp;Islam is that its&nbsp;precivilized.&nbsp;&nbsp;But in reality, it is quite civilized.. and the only reason it hasn't had a chance&nbsp;to modernize is because foreign hands.. throughout history ... never let it develop truly into the Islam it could have.&nbsp;&nbsp;And even deeper, the foreign Imperial powers in certain moments of history&nbsp; actually intentionally made sure that development in the Arabic empires were halted... but I'll share those another time. 

However, Islam has a strong identity and had it not been tampered with by the penetration of the Imperial great powers ... I feel..&nbsp;could very well have modernized in a very beautiful&nbsp;Islamic&nbsp;fashion.&nbsp;&nbsp;

Well, I&nbsp;need to sleep&nbsp;but I will blog more about what I&nbsp;have learned thus&nbsp;far of&nbsp;Islam later.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;

My econ teacher said bold and proudly, &quot;Look at each one of your lives and see the product of your decisions.&quot;&nbsp; The truth in that stings.&nbsp; Every single decision we make leads to where we each are now and whom we are.&nbsp; He also said, and a many other teachers/advisors I've had; 

There are two types of people in this world.&nbsp; There are winners.&nbsp; And there are losers.&nbsp; Most often than not, the winners win at the expense of the losers.&nbsp; But then again, if you don't want to be a loser&nbsp;then do what you must to become a winner.&nbsp;&nbsp; 

&nbsp;

1999? 2000? 


So there I&nbsp;was, at this thing called the rocks.&nbsp; Well, we always referred to it as the rocks but really the rocks were the harbor near lake Michigan.&nbsp; Our partying moved from harbor to harbor as we got kicked from one to the next.&nbsp; I cannot emphasize enough the amount of drugs that the beautiful rocks have ever seen.&nbsp; 

So there I was, my&nbsp;second time here.&nbsp; Party all night and then come here.&nbsp; That's how this worked, and so it went for a year.&nbsp; Maybe more, or less, who can tell when time was not here.&nbsp; I don't even remember who I&nbsp;went there with, maybe it was Megan maybe this is where I&nbsp;had met my Fozzie dear.&nbsp; What I do remember is sitting beside a crowd of people, still feeling the drugs of the night.&nbsp;&nbsp;Silence from all except from the dancing of the waves at&nbsp;4 a.m.&nbsp;&nbsp;All was dead around except for their sound.&nbsp; Not that much later till I&nbsp;saw the peek of&nbsp;a&nbsp;faded orange from the sun.&nbsp;&nbsp; 

Let me digress,&nbsp;and try not to glamorize.&nbsp; But in this moment my soul began to transform.&nbsp; I went from frightened and weak&nbsp;to someone who can speak.&nbsp; I&nbsp;was&nbsp;able to shake some hands and right away make friends rather than&nbsp;always be locked&nbsp;within my shell.&nbsp; I mean it when I&nbsp;say&nbsp;I don't hold too many regrets.&nbsp; And as much as this&nbsp;moment of my demise&nbsp;let so many&nbsp;opportunities slip by, I&nbsp;needed this to be who I&nbsp;am.&nbsp; I&nbsp;never&nbsp;lost the social butterfly&nbsp;I had learned to be then.&nbsp; And more, the lessons I impart from then will&nbsp;always be inside now.&nbsp; The truth is drugs made me submit to my fears and forget.&nbsp; And not just that, drugs opened doors to my soul that well.. will never close now.&nbsp; I will explain another time.&nbsp; Let me revisit the moment of that sunrise.&nbsp; 

A bunch of strangers sitting so close to each other all observing the most&nbsp;beautiful ever.&nbsp;&nbsp;As the minutes&nbsp;passed us by more colors began to fly - reds, oranges, yellows&nbsp;absorbing the dark sky.&nbsp; The cold reminding us just how much we are alive.&nbsp; In that moment, I&nbsp;remember&nbsp;I&nbsp;wanted to do nothing more but cry.&nbsp; The meaning of life right before my eyes.&nbsp;&nbsp;The meaning of life!&nbsp; Yes, right before my eyes.&nbsp; It's too bad it took me up until now to realize what I felt and didnt understand then.&nbsp; 

And then the sky turned bright and more&nbsp;kids had come along with&nbsp;them a ton of bads.&nbsp;&nbsp;A menu of&nbsp;things that&nbsp;included lots of&nbsp;things&nbsp;beginning with &nbsp;A,&nbsp;C, E, H&nbsp;and M.&nbsp; Over the years, the big K&nbsp;too had made its way.&nbsp; But those stories will&nbsp;have to come another time. 

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

Hmm.. this sudden outburst to storytell events of my past.. is not.. me dwelling on anything.&nbsp; Rather, I've recently had a turn of events that made me realize just how much I've lived.&nbsp; How grateful I&nbsp;am for all those valuable lessons, how I&nbsp;have begun to understand the puzzle that I am. &nbsp;

How much writing is a very big part of who I am.&nbsp; And as an author, it's not just.. things I create that matter.&nbsp; It's my life that matters.&nbsp; Because my experiences as wild and crazy as they have been.. are the greatest inspirations of any story I&nbsp;can ever come to create.&nbsp; Some of my own life stories, are greater than anything I&nbsp;could ever create.&nbsp; They are real.&nbsp; They hold valuable lessons that not just I&nbsp;can apply. &nbsp;

No.&nbsp; This year, I&nbsp;dwell on nothing.&nbsp; I&nbsp;think, for once I&nbsp;can say Im finally moving on.&nbsp; I'm just a writer, who needs to make it permanent.&nbsp; Paint exactly what I'm moving on from.

This year ... I am graduating.&nbsp; I'm a mother.&nbsp; And I'm going to the big U.&nbsp; And I have never been more driven.&nbsp; Especially, driven to write.&nbsp; As much as I say I&nbsp;should be farther in life... I've come to realize, just how far I&nbsp;have come. &nbsp;&nbsp; 

This year... I am so confident.&nbsp; I know I am beautiful.&nbsp; So smart.&nbsp; But what's more beautiful, is my journey.&nbsp; The start.&nbsp; How could I not want to write about that?&nbsp;

I feel good lately.&nbsp; Totally inspired.&nbsp; And more so.. such clarity.&nbsp; Each day I&nbsp;keep discovering more and more lessons and insights.&nbsp; In various ways.&nbsp; Philosophical, metaphorical, emotional, mental, historical.&nbsp; I've been reading a lot.&nbsp; Currently, reading Vidal's Dreaming War.&nbsp; I suppose I could share opinion on it however it is things I've said before.&nbsp; 

I've said my bit on the War for oil.&nbsp; I've also said my bit, I&nbsp;think, about the inaccurate account of bombing of Hiroshima, and Pearl Harbor.&nbsp; I&nbsp;have not talked about the inaccuracies of the Cold war.. but heh I wont.&nbsp; Might have my head bitten off.&nbsp; That's a topic of taboo as well.&nbsp; Anyway.. vidal is an incredible writer.&nbsp; And I'm almost done with this book.&nbsp; Next on my agenda is another book of his called Building an Imperial nation, or something of the sort.&nbsp; Can't live without my history. &nbsp;

Afterall, what is the future without our past?&nbsp; What lessons can we embrace without knowing their birth place?&nbsp; Our mistakes are treasures in the palm of our hands.&nbsp; 

And Monday, I&nbsp;start where I&nbsp;left off.&nbsp; Back to school I&nbsp;go!&nbsp; More people to meet, more things to learn.&nbsp; Life is somewhat good.&nbsp; Except!&nbsp; My roots are showing, and the red is fading.&nbsp; Time to dye my head. &nbsp;

So, I&nbsp;will admit.&nbsp; I&nbsp;have been avoiding the chapter of my darkest days.&nbsp; I get shaken looking back at those times.&nbsp; And in fact, took me a night to find a way to talk about.&nbsp; I cannot glamorize it because there is no glamour in it.&nbsp; Parts of those times I dont even want to remember because.. well they are just so bad.&nbsp; But how can any person be fully whole without truly being able to look back at their lives, fearless and do nothing but simply nod.&nbsp; I acknowledge it.&nbsp; And now, I'm learning from it.&nbsp; Forever.

So alrite! Let's go back, to the beginning.&nbsp; The night I&nbsp;shared that kiss with Lucifer, the night I&nbsp;was taken aback by the long line around the abandoned warehouse.&nbsp; The goofy looking kids, and the electronic music with the constant pounding beats.&nbsp; And let it be known, the first night I did no drugs.&nbsp; The experience alone was enough to be my drug.&nbsp; This party went all night and not once did it ever take a break.&nbsp; Music kept on till the sunlight.&nbsp; And even then, sweat-filled kids with baggy pants kept dancing to the beats.&nbsp;&nbsp;

There were girls and boys, with huge baggy pants that by the night were half wet and filled with mud... hot pink shirts on girls, and rainbow colored beads all over their wrists.&nbsp; In fact I will say I saw boys too, dressed like this.&nbsp; Looking back on it now, I can honestly say the house of Rave was one that bore no judgement on anything.&nbsp; Wether you were gay or straight, ugly or beautiful, shy or not, thin or fat.&nbsp; Noone cared.&nbsp; All they cared about was having fun.&nbsp; Dancing the night away.&nbsp; And, soon enough I learned, to do lots of drugs. 

The house of Rave had its own segment of transformation.&nbsp; As did each and every person there.&nbsp; It's as if the Rave scene was a living thing.&nbsp; Growing and falling, living and breathing.&nbsp; An everchanging culture.&nbsp; And yes, that culture was defined by electronic music but lets not be naive and deny the influence of drugs.&nbsp; I recount in my last days of that scene conversations with people preaching, &quot;It's not only about drugs. &nbsp;It's the music.&nbsp; It should only be about the music&quot; Only to find them secretly sniffing coke in the backroom of the dance floor.&nbsp; Not about drugs you say? 

My theory of the transformation of the scene I&nbsp;always felt was come about via the influence of the type of drugs introduced.&nbsp; In the beginning, there was house and ecstacy and acid.&nbsp; Rainbow kids with rainbows in their eyes.&nbsp; But as time went by, and I cannot tell you how much for recounting 'time' from that era is impossible.&nbsp; Time was dead back then.&nbsp; But, however long has passed a new drug arose.&nbsp; Something called 'K&quot; and more popularity in cocaine.&nbsp; And towards the end, a huge popularity in crystal meth.&nbsp; Not saying these drugs were not around the whole time but merely rose in popularity during different times.&nbsp; What I'm saying is drugs have a different sort of effect and with abuse effect personality.&nbsp; Ecstacy makes you happy and free, loving everbody hell maybe even a tree.&nbsp; But it gets old and after a while grows very hard to recover from.&nbsp; K, or also known as animal tranquilizer found in the office of your veterninarian, had a whole new effect.&nbsp; A sort of .. paralyzing and dimming senses effect.&nbsp; Made the time continuum stop before your eyes.&nbsp; And if you did enough, an out of body experience can come about.&nbsp; Through much usage I&nbsp;noticed it made people so mean and sour.&nbsp; Turned them as I called them back then.. evil.&nbsp; How do you think much of this stuff came to people's hands?&nbsp; An increased breaking into veterninarians had arose.&nbsp; Of which a close friend of mine was put in jail for.&nbsp; And then there was cocaine and heroine.&nbsp; Yea, you can see someone be very mean on that.&nbsp; Especially, once their addictions began to kick in. &nbsp;&nbsp; 

I dont think I can go on.&nbsp; Chapter over, for now.&nbsp; I just.. cannot write about this right now.&nbsp; Maybe its fear of judgement.&nbsp; Maybe its fear of my own judgement.&nbsp; And yet.. the era of those times have so many explanations and lessons of the person I have come to be.&nbsp; Of what I conquered, from my childhood and the past.&nbsp; And the things I still have a hard time about. &nbsp;

Responsibility, I gained from conquering all that.&nbsp; Living life in moderation, like Aristotle spoke about.&nbsp; All these valuable lessons that have come to me, I want to know where their birth came from to me. I don't even know why I&nbsp;want to write about all this, and yet.. this urge like it has to be.&nbsp; 

But I can confidently say I hate these drugs, and wish they were never around.&nbsp; Because as whole as I&nbsp;am now, I put my mind through some hell.&nbsp; More damage has been done.&nbsp; Sure lessons.&nbsp; But at what cost.&nbsp; And now that I've seen the potential of that pandora's box how could I not worry as a mother, knowing how well within reach that box has become. &nbsp;

And then.. I&nbsp;realize.&nbsp; I had no mother or a guiding light.&nbsp; I&nbsp;had noone.&nbsp; Maybe that is the root of where it all begun.&nbsp; Chapter over.

 &nbsp; 

&nbsp;

Friends come and go, but there are those that never go.&nbsp; Friends forever till the end.&nbsp; I've never been good with relationships, be it romantic or friend.&nbsp; I've always had this inner tendency to run from things when things got close.&nbsp; Like a frightened rabbit I tremble and run the moment I felt something strong, a bond; a connection; love; a sort of commitment.&nbsp; I've been running most my life, in fact a part of me inside still does.&nbsp; I've tried to tackle my trust defect and yet it is very hard.&nbsp; The outside world never made it easy.&nbsp; Throughout these chapters of my past I will paint more clarity of that part. &nbsp;&nbsp; 

But there are a few of my friends that stuck around, despite the complicated person I've always been.&nbsp; There's Aimee, the one who holds nothing back.&nbsp; The one, who has always known how to make me laugh.&nbsp; There's Kristin, the one who wouldn't dare let me walk away - she's seen some of my darkest days.&nbsp; And even now that she's married, I know she will be here for me.&nbsp; And she was.&nbsp; And she is.&nbsp; There's many chapters of the segments of our friendship.&nbsp; And in them all, she's always been my guiding light.&nbsp; There's my faraway friend, who knows me more than I know myself.&nbsp; In fact, may know things about me that neither Aimee nor Kristin can ever even begin to understand.&nbsp; Things, that I&nbsp;only now begin to understand.&nbsp; 

But I'm merely skimming through the chapters of my life right now.&nbsp;&nbsp; And in a little while, I'll begin with where we all began.. my high school years.&nbsp;

It's so beautiful outside... unable to sleep I look out and see the beauty of the moonlight shining its life upon the ever so graceful snow... the snow that paints our grounds white once more.&nbsp; 

God.&nbsp; It's so beautiful.&nbsp; Makes me want to cry, how much something as simple as a snowflake contains the power to stir in me such emotion.&nbsp; Because that snowflake bears so much memory of where I been and where I'm&nbsp; headed.&nbsp; That snowflake contains winters among winters of past that hold so much memory of where I been.&nbsp; 

The love's I held, the people I held.. the love I still remember ... the love's I can't ever dare let go... the days of my unhappiness... the day of my lonely childhood... the day's of my struggles... my many smiles and my many tears ... the days of my ultimate happiness... my broken heart... the same roads ... the roads I still continue to turn too .. my life.


And throughout my journey... one thing is clear.&nbsp; There is a fire within me that burns... that has and always will burn... my passions... my love of being alive.. perhaps the only thing setting me free... knowing... we are never really ever or will ever be free.&nbsp; Perhaps its precisely this fire that is the very thing that entraps me yet...it is my wine... my reason to be... to live... to breathe... to create.&nbsp; 

the world is beautiful outside right now as the ground shines. ..

Happy Late turkey day everyone!&nbsp; 

This was the first year where I did not get in a huge tear-filled argument on thanksgiving.. thank goodness.&nbsp; So I guess, it was an ok thanksgiving.&nbsp; I haven't really update LJ lately because every year the holiday season brings me a small hint of depression.&nbsp; Granted.. this year is a little bit less chaotic in terms of arguing and hurtful words towards one another... yet... this year's holiday season I cant help but feel a sense of emptiness.. unfulfillment ... and a horrible loneliness.&nbsp; Why loneliness? I have no clue.. Im surrounded by people.. 


I'm less free this year... but it's alrite in time I will get my freedom back.&nbsp; So many unfilled things that I have yet to accomplish.&nbsp; In time.&nbsp; I&nbsp;will. 

Man.. the winter blues are coming early this year for me =/.&nbsp; 

One thing I&nbsp;am learning this year.. is just how much I love to laugh.&nbsp; And joke.&nbsp; And.. man laughter makes me feel so good lately.&nbsp; I love that I've been able to laugh and smile a bit more than the previous years.&nbsp; 

So this blog is completely pointless but I&nbsp;havent put a word in my lj in a bit... so obligated to write something.&nbsp; Maybe when the blue inside me settles down I'll write something more meaningful. 

Adieu!&nbsp;
